Add, rename, or delete a breakout session
As a host or cohost, you can add or delete breakout sessions before the sessions are started. You can change the name of a breakout session at any time.
This feature is supported on Webex Meetings and Webex Webinars. On Webex App, this feature is available on our Video Mesh-ready meeting platform.
A maximum of 100 breakout sessions can be added to meeting.
Desktop
iOS
Android
1
If the Breakout session assignments dialog box isn't already open, click Breakout sessions to open it.

  Only one host or cohost can have the Breakout session assignment dialog box open at a time.
2
Choose to add, rename, or delete a breakout session:
To add a breakout session, click Add session, and then enter a new name for the session or press Enter to use the default name.
Assign participants to this session or move participants from another session into this one.
To rename a breakout session, hover over the session name, click Rename, and then enter a new name.
To delete a breakout session, hover over the breakout session, and then click Delete.
All participants in the session will be unassigned.